A BILL FOR AN ACT
To amend 9 CMC §8209 by removing the seven-day grace
period for motorists who violate 9 CMC §§8203 and 8204 with
the citation effective immediately; and for other purposes.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE 24TH NORTHERN MARIANAS
COMMONWEALTH LEGISLATURE:
1 Section 1. Findings and Purpose. The Legislature finds that motorists
2 must be dutiful and responsible for the safety and security of our local roads. A
3 valid license, registration, and insurance are required documentation that ensure
4 compliance and assure road safety. Immediate fines are enforced once motorists are
5 found without valid license or registration on their person when operating a vehicle.
6 This is not the case for valid vehicle liability insurance. Not having consistent
7 enforcement with all the required documentation dampens compliance and safety
8 measures, especially since road incidents and their damages are unpredictable in
9 both occurrence and the extent of the damages. Having no insurance as a motorist
10 may also bear heavy financial risk and loss for parties involved should an accident
11 or injury occur. Therefore, having valid insurance should bear the same emphasis
12 as other required documents for vehicle operation.

